FBIS4-17224 "drsov078_f_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 National Affairs Cabinet: Managers Responsible for Gas Payments Cabinet: Managers Responsible for Gas Payments WS2104161794 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 1400 GMT 21 Apr 94 WS2104161794 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Ukrainian BFN [Text] We received a report today from the press service of the Ukrainian president and the Ukrainian Cabinet of Ministers. Who will pay for gas? The government is referring to nonpayments for Russian gas used by Ukrainian enterprises. An agreement on settling Ukraine's gas debts in the sum of $500 million was reached with the leadership of the Russian joint stock company Gasprom. [Words indistinct] over the first three months of the current year, our enterprises paid only 20-25 percent of the required amount. Considering this situation, acting Prime Minister Yukhym Zvyahilskyy today held an extended meeting with leaders of certain ministries and departments, representatives of oblast administrations, and managers of production associations which amass enormous gas debts. Opportunities for the branches and enterprises, in particular the Ministry of Industry and the Ministry of [word indistinct] to clear their debts at the expense of their production were discussed. Specific measures aimed at making payments next month -- which must be carried out under the personal responsibility of enterprise managers -- were also detailed at this meeting. The oblast state administration was authorized to pressure debtor enterprises. If they fail to make these payments, managers of enterprises and local administrations will bear all responsibility for the economic and social (?consequences), which may follow after gas deliveries to enterprises, which have not cleared their gas debts, are suspended.
